\begin_layout Plain Layout
It strikes me how technology is almost exclusively associated with performance
 and efficiency.
 How, as knowledge workers, getting better tools to accomplish more and
 more difficult and complex tasks, our satisfaction towards our efficiency
 is not increasing.
 Instead, technology often makes us see all the tasks that we are unable
 to accomplish in one day.
 Email is operating 24h a day while we clearly cannot.
 Overall, we try to adapt to the tools we have instead of them being adapted
 to our humane nature.
 As the form factor of our computational devices gets increasingly personal
 -- smartphones and smartwatches are quickly becoming ubiquitous and are
 with us all the time -- it is important to reflect on the effect they have
 in our lives.
 For the most part, they are greatly beneficial as they allow us to stay
 connected with loved ones, access to a wealth of information, work, play,
 etc.
