\begin_layout Standard
Using a co-design approach, we intervened in a scientific museum over two
 half days, proposing to passersby to try out Tobe.
 We built the sensors and prepared the signal processing beforehand because
 these steps require hardware and expertise.
 Five high-level metrics were selected: workload, vigilance, meditation,
 valence and arousal.
 These metrics were chosen because the wide public showed interest into
 them (meditation and emotions) or because they could benefit from being
 better known (workload and vigilance).
 Due to the short duration of our exhibitions, we also set the corresponding
 feedback (both support and shape), according to the outcome of the questionnair
