 and the resulting state has positive impact on well-being 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "McCraty2009"

\end_inset

.
 During cardiac coherence, HR increases slightly when one inhales and decreases
 as much when one exhales.
 We took the magnitude squared coherence between HR and breathing signals
 over 10s time windows as a "relaxation" index.
\end_layout

